# MQTT Protocol

Expert guidance for MQTT protocol implementation in the EWM Robotic Platform.

## Auto-Apply Triggers
- When implementing MQTT topics for Hikrobot AGV communication
- When configuring QoS levels (0, 1, 2) for message delivery guarantees
- When designing Pub/Sub patterns for multi-robot coordination
- When managing MQTT connection lifecycle with auto-reconnect
- When setting up message retention or Last Will and Testament

## Activation Commands
→ "Configure MQTT topics for Hikrobot AGV task dispatch"
→ "Implement MQTT connection with auto-reconnect and exponential backoff"
→ "Set up QoS 2 for critical task assignment messages"
→ "Add Last Will and Testament for robot offline detection"

## EWM Platform Integration
- Topic hierarchy: ewm/robots/{id}/, ewm/tasks/, ewm/sap/
- QoS 0: telemetry (position, battery)
- QoS 1: status updates, alerts
- QoS 2: task dispatch, order completion
- LWT for offline detection
- Auto-reconnect with exponential backoff
